/**
 * SHOWROOM-TRUTH-FIX: the Trade showcase's demo rows, GENERATED by the real
 * scoring engine — not hand-typed.
 *
 * The SHOWROOM-TRUTH-AUDIT found the old hand-typed NO-TRADE row contradicted
 * the engine three ways (miscounted its own gates; showed NO TRADE where the
 * engine gives a 20% marginal position; showed a null composite that is
 * impossible with four scored gates). The fix: the demo DECLARES three fully
 * synthetic inputs (fictional tickers, invented-but-plausible market data,
 * one shared macro snapshot exactly like a real scan) and calls the REAL pure
 * scorer `scoreAll` (src/lib/convergence/composite.ts:118) on them at module
 * load. Every score, the composite, the gate-count caption
 * (`composite.convergence_gate` — the engine's own string, verbatim), the
 * position size, the strategy suggestion, and the survival-brake state below
 * are ENGINE OUTPUT. The demo cannot drift from the engine again: if the
 * engine's rules change, these rows change with it at the next build.
 *
 * TRIPWIRE HELD: this file only CALLS the engine — no engine logic changed.
 * The inputs are static fiction (zero fetches, zero paid calls, nothing
 * personal — the SHOW discipline of TabShowcases.tsx); only the SCORING is
 * real. scoreAll is pure (no I/O — see composite.ts imports), so calling it
 * client-side is side-effect-free; the cost is bundling the scorer (~the same
 * page already ships the full ConvergenceIntelligence surface).
 */

